This paper deals with machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training classifiers and using them to tag data, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the use of metrics to analyze the models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions analyzing the train-data tagging process, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
